# Backup files
*.backup
*.bak

# OS generated files
Thumbs.db

# ── Stateful Graphiti / runtime isolation ────────────────────────────────────
# Keep dynamic execution state out of the SSOT clone so guarded auto-sync stays
# fast-forward-clean and never collides with these per-machine/per-run files.
# NOTE: memory-bank/ (per-project scaffold) is ignored; ops/graphiti/memory-bank-template/
# is the tracked source and is intentionally NOT matched by this pattern.
memory-bank/
.workflow_state_*.json
*.fallback.log
.cursor-globalcommands-fallback.log
.backup.*

*.pyc
__pycache__/

# ── Self-referential workspace wiring (SSOT repo is not its own "consumer" repo) ──
# setup_workspace_symlinks.sh can be run from inside ~/.cursor-governance itself,
# which creates a symlink pointing to itself plus a local .cursor/ dir. Harmless,
# but must never be committed — the SSOT clone is a source, not a consumer.
/.cursor-commands
/.cursor/

# ── Credential-shaped files that must never be committed ────────────────────
# 2026-07-21: session-end governance sync hook auto-staged a live Google OAuth
# client secret from WIP/google_oauth_*.json (not pushed; caught + removed
# before it reached origin). These patterns stop the hook from re-adding them.
WIP/*oauth*.json
WIP/*credentials*.json
WIP/*client_secret*.json
